item.title: [HBASE-7797] Use consistent package name
item.description:
This has been discussed here: http://search-hadoop.com/m/bXxiV1MGsYi2.

We should not release 0.96 with two namespaces. This will cause further pain and confusion in the future (like log4j configuration, greping logs, etc).

As much as I like it, I don't see us going o.a.hbase namespace, so let's move the Cell, and prefix tree classes to o.a.hadoop.hbase.

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: let me know what to do. i can make a patch, but might be just as simple for a committer to drag the files in an IDE

To keep the history, it is better to do this using svn mv manually. Oh how much I hate svn.
I am up for this, as long as there is no objection.

In the above discussion it was acknowledged that HBase, being a top level project, should have its own namespace.
Is a whole scale change across all files the only way of achieving that goal ?

If we move gradually, there would be a window during which there're two namespaces. I think such window should be allowed.

In the above discussion it was acknowledged that HBase, being a top level project, should have its own namespace.

True. HBase should be using o.a.hbase.

Is a whole scale change across all files the only way of achieving that goal ?

In this patch, I am not suggesting we migrate to o.a.hbase. The opposite.

I think we can revisit this decision while preparing for 1.0 or after trunk becomes 2.0.

I understand what this JIRA proposes.
I was thinking how we can migrate to o.a.hbase in one shot.
Currently we have:

trunk tyu$ find . -name '*.java' | wc
1521 1521 133734

By the time we prepare 1.0 or 2.0, there would be ~2000 files. We should think about the following questions:
1. who would migrate ~2000 files in matter of day - more than one. We can partition the work among volunteers.
2. how long trunk should be frozen so that this renaming can be completed without many rebasings

If we have clear plan, I am fine with reverting to single namespace for now.
If you are looking for some hands to move to o.a.hbase, you can count on me.
Is it such an issue having two namespaces?

Sorry, let me say more.

As I see it, Cell Interface is a new grounding for our fundamental type. I was thinking to emphasize this new beginning, I thought it worth setting it apart by making it the first inhabitant of our rightful namespace.

I can see the intention, but Cell is a small part of the overall client API. Is there a plan to gradually move the other parts of the API to the new namespace, or rewrite v2 APIs? If not, then we might as well end up with 2 namespaces for years, which I am trying to avoid. This looks like the mapred vs mapreduce set of APIs, but the difference is that mapreduce mostly replaces the whole mapred namespace, whereas Cell is not.
Having said that, if we plan to migrate filters, coprocessors, htable, etc for the new Cell interface and keep the BC versions in place we might as well document it and close this one as invalid.
